{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7540dadf-e71c-4589-8493-9edb9aa30c27","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results rather than failing or passing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eedfd7aa-c000-4725-97c9-33f40327497f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip/ignore tests with a reason message in four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":214,"requestId":"BD0A:2DE6FB:1CFF94A:20B21C5:6A07C4EC"},"id":"87c79bb5-99ab-40bf-8813-069d742f550d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:25.530Z","parentId":"9ff337ed-bcab-4b43-a72d-382909e95303"}
